- I examined app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostController::index — it returns a paginated collection of PostResource items: PostResource::collection(Post::search(...)->withCount('comments')->latest()->paginate(...)).
- I inspected app/Http/Resources/Post.php to determine each post item structure. Each item includes: id (int), title (string), slug (string), content (string), posted_at (ISO8601 datetime string), author_id (int), comments_count (int), and two conditional thumbnail URL fields thumbnail_url and thumb_thumbnail_url (strings present only when a thumbnail exists).
- I checked tests/tests/Feature/Api/V1/PostTest.php which asserts the JSON structure for the index endpoint. The expected top-level response is a paginated object containing: data (array of post items), links (object with first, last, prev, next), and meta (pagination metadata: current_page, from, last_page, path, per_page, to, total).
- Based on the controller, resource, and tests, the GET /v1/posts response for a successful request is HTTP 200 with a JSON body shaped as a pagination wrapper containing data, links and meta. I modeled the Response Object in Swagger 2.0 style without $ref, explicitly listing the schema for the whole response, the post item fields, links and meta fields. Fields that are conditionally present (thumbnail_url and thumb_thumbnail_url) are included as optional (not in required list). Some pagination numbers (from, to, prev links) may be null — types allow null (expressed as ["string","null"] or ["integer","null"]).

